1
00:00:34,442 --> 00:00:38,570
WOODS NEAR QUANTICO, VA

2
00:02:47,168 --> 00:02:49,208
Starling!

3
00:02:50,797 --> 00:02:52,836
Starling!

4
00:02:54,926 --> 00:02:57,842
Crawford wants to see you in his office.

5
00:02:57,969 --> 00:03:00,009
Thank you, sir.

6
00:03:47,348 --> 00:03:49,387
- Clarice.
- Hey.

7
00:04:39,698 --> 00:04:44,692
You looking for Crawford? He should
be back in a minute. Wait in his office.

8
00:05:41,629 --> 00:05:43,705
Starling.

9
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:47,254
- Clarice M. Good morning.
- Morning, Mr Crawford.

10
00:05:47,383 --> 00:05:50,764
Sorry to pull you off the course
at such short notice.

11
00:05:50,899 --> 00:05:54,102
Your instructors tell me you're doing well.

12
00:05:54,236 --> 00:05:57,355
I hope so. They haven't
posted any grades yet.

13
00:05:57,656 --> 00:06:00,229
A job's come up and I thought about you.

14
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:04,778
Not a job, really. More of
an interesting errand. Sit down.

15
00:06:04,912 --> 00:06:06,739
Yes, sir.

16
00:06:06,872 --> 00:06:12,956
I remember you from my seminar at UVA.
You grilled me pretty hard, as I recall,

17
00:06:13,085 --> 00:06:17,083
on the Bureau's civil rights record
in the Hoover years. I gave you an A.

18
00:06:17,215 --> 00:06:19,670
A-minus, sir.

19
00:06:21,301 --> 00:06:24,468
Double major: Psych and criminology.
Graduated magna.

20
00:06:24,596 --> 00:06:27,383
Summer internships
at the Reitzinger Clinic.

21
00:06:27,515 --> 00:06:32,391
It says, when you graduate, you wanna
work for me in Behavioural Science.

22
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,560
Yes, very much, sir. Very much.

23
00:06:36,107 --> 00:06:40,934
We're interviewing all serial killers now in
custody for a psycho-behavioural profile.

24
00:06:41,069 --> 00:06:43,690
Could be a real help in unsolved cases.

25
00:06:43,821 --> 00:06:46,359
Most of them have been
happy to talk to us.

26
00:06:46,824 --> 00:06:50,952
- Do you spook easily, Starling?
- Not yet, sir.

27
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:53,864
See, the one we want most
refuses to cooperate.

28
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:56,784
I want you to go after him
again today in the asylum.

29
00:06:56,916 --> 00:07:00,961
- Who's the subject?
- The psychiatrist, Hannibal Lecter.

30
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,329
Hannibal the Cannibal.

31
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:06,134
I don't expect him to talk to you.

32
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:09,876
But I have to be able to say we tried.

33
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:13,131
So if he won't cooperate,
I want just straight reporting.

34
00:07:13,265 --> 00:07:16,848
How does he look? How does
his cell look? Is he sketching, drawing?

35
00:07:16,977 --> 00:07:19,646
If he is, what's he sketching?

36
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:25,402
Here's a dossier on Lecter.

37
00:07:27,653 --> 00:07:31,164
A copy of our questionnaire
and a special ID for you.

38
00:07:31,294 --> 00:07:33,963
Have your memo on my desk
by 0800 Wednesday.

39
00:07:34,088 --> 00:07:36,127
OK.

40
00:07:37,757 --> 00:07:42,715
Excuse me, sir, but why the urgency?
Lecter's been in prison for so many years.

41
00:07:42,846 --> 00:07:46,178
Is there some connection
between him and Buffalo Bill maybe?

42
00:07:46,306 --> 00:07:51,051
I wish there were.
Now, I want your full attention, Starling.

43
00:07:51,185 --> 00:07:54,637
- Yes, sir.
- Be very careful with Hannibal Lecter.

44
00:07:55,147 --> 00:07:59,691
Dr Chilton at the asylum will go over all
the physical procedures used with him.

45
00:07:59,819 --> 00:08:03,436
Do not deviate from them
for any reason whatsoever.

46
00:08:03,571 --> 00:08:06,145
And you're to tell him nothing personal.

47
00:08:06,282 --> 00:08:09,865
Believe me, you don't want
Hannibal Lecter inside your head.

48
00:08:09,994 --> 00:08:13,031
Just do your job,
but never forget what he is.

49
00:08:13,164 --> 00:08:14,195
And what is that?

50
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:18,662
Oh, he's a monster. A pure psychopath.

51
00:08:19,169 --> 00:08:21,328
So rare to capture one alive.

52
00:08:21,463 --> 00:08:25,959
From a research point of view,
Lecter is our most prized asset.

53
00:08:29,804 --> 00:08:34,928
We get a lot of detectives here, but
I can't ever remember one as attractive.

54
00:08:37,102 --> 00:08:39,806
Will you be in Baltimore overnight?

55
00:08:39,938 --> 00:08:45,063
Because this can be quite a fun town
if you have the right guide.

56
00:08:45,193 --> 00:08:47,399
I'm sure this is a great town, Dr Chilton,

57
00:08:47,529 --> 00:08:52,948
but my instructions are to talk to Dr Lecter
and report back this afternoon.

58
00:08:53,075 --> 00:08:56,407
I see. Well, let's make this quick, then.

59
00:08:56,535 --> 00:09:01,281
We've tried to study him, but he's much
too sophisticated for the standard tests.

60
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:03,704
Oh, my, does he hate us!

61
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:07,084
He thinks I'm his nemesis.

62
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:10,303
Crawford's very clever,
isn't he, using you?

63
00:09:10,435 --> 00:09:14,729
- What do you mean, sir?
- A pretty, young woman to turn him on.

64
00:09:15,231 --> 00:09:17,936
I don't believe Lecter's
seen a woman in eight years.

65
00:09:18,068 --> 00:09:21,935
And are you ever his taste! So to speak.

66
00:09:22,072 --> 00:09:25,072
I graduated from UVA, Doctor.
It's not a charm school.

67
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:28,817
Good. Then you should
be able to remember the rules.

68
00:09:31,371 --> 00:09:35,369
Do not touch or approach the glass.
You pass him nothing but soft paper.

69
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:39,249
No pencils or pens.
No staples or paperclips in his paper.

70
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:44,171
Use the sliding food carrier. If he attempts
to pass you anything, do not accept it.

71
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:47,965
- Do you understand me?
- Yes, I understand, sir.

72
00:09:48,304 --> 00:09:51,424
I'm going to show you
why we insist on such precautions.

73
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:57,144
On July 8, 1981, he complained of chest
pains and was taken to the dispensary.

74
00:09:57,271 --> 00:09:59,939
His restraints were removed for an EKG.

75
00:10:00,064 --> 00:10:03,812
When the nurse leaned over him,
he did this to her.

76
00:10:05,777 --> 00:10:10,523
The doctors managed to reset her jaw,
more or less, save one of her eyes.

77
00:10:10,657 --> 00:10:15,236
His pulse never got above 85,
even when he ate her tongue.

78
00:10:16,162 --> 00:10:18,949
- I keep him in here.
- Dr Chilton.

79
00:10:22,251 --> 00:10:24,492
If Lecter feels that you're his enemy,

80
00:10:24,627 --> 00:10:29,585
then maybe we'll have more luck
if I go in by myself. What do you think?

81
00:10:32,843 --> 00:10:37,754
You might have suggested this
in my office and saved me the time.

82
00:10:37,889 --> 00:10:43,131
Yes, sir, but then I would have missed
the pleasure of your company, sir.

83
00:10:45,229 --> 00:10:48,146
When she's finished, bring her out.

84
00:11:15,893 --> 00:11:20,354
Hi, I'm Barney. He told you,
don't get near the glass?

85
00:11:20,898 --> 00:11:23,518
Yes, he did. Clarice Starling.

86
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:27,648
Nice to meet you, Clarice. You can
hang your coat up there if you like.

87
00:11:27,779 --> 00:11:30,234
Thank you. I will.

88
00:11:31,282 --> 00:11:33,856
He's past the others, the last cell.

89
00:11:33,993 --> 00:11:36,449
You keep to the right.

90
00:11:38,164 --> 00:11:42,327
- I put out a chair for you.
- That's very good. Thank you.

91
00:11:43,460 --> 00:11:46,544
I'll be watchin'. You'll do fine.

92
00:11:57,264 --> 00:11:59,304
Hi.

93
00:12:17,491 --> 00:12:19,946
I can smell your cunt!

94
00:12:33,225 --> 00:12:36,844
- Good morning.
- Dr Lecter, my name is Clarice Starling.

95
00:12:36,979 --> 00:12:38,853
May I speak with you?

96
00:12:38,981 --> 00:12:41,602
You're one of Jack Crawford's,
aren't you?

97
00:12:41,734 --> 00:12:45,981
- I am, yes.
- May I see your credentials?

98
00:12:46,614 --> 00:12:48,652
Certainly.

99
00:12:54,954 --> 00:12:57,409
Closer, please.

100
00:12:58,415 --> 00:13:00,075
Closer.

101
00:13:15,847 --> 00:13:20,390
That expires in one week.
You're not real FBI, are you?

102
00:13:20,935 --> 00:13:23,341
I'm still in training at the academy.

103
00:13:24,478 --> 00:13:27,432
Jack Crawford sent a trainee to me?

104
00:13:27,732 --> 00:13:31,776
Yes, I'm a student.
I'm here to learn from you.

105
00:13:31,902 --> 00:13:36,860
Maybe you can decide whether or not
I'm qualified enough to do that.

106
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:41,653
That is rather slippery of you,
Agent Starling.

107
00:13:45,248 --> 00:13:47,703
Sit, please.

108
00:13:54,215 --> 00:13:58,212
Now then, tell me.
What did Miggs say to you?

109
00:13:58,343 --> 00:14:01,048
Multiple Miggs in the next cell.

110
00:14:01,179 --> 00:14:04,382
He hissed at you. What did he say?

111
00:14:05,809 --> 00:14:08,726
He said "I can smell your cunt."

112
00:14:09,062 --> 00:14:11,612
I see.

113
00:14:11,743 --> 00:14:14,198
I myself cannot.

114
00:14:22,795 --> 00:14:25,250
You use Evyan skin cream.

115
00:14:27,925 --> 00:14:30,877
And sometimes you wear L'Air du Temps.

116
00:14:32,219 --> 00:14:34,674
But not today.

117
00:14:36,014 --> 00:14:38,684
Did you do all these drawings, Doctor?

118
00:14:40,852 --> 00:14:44,138
That is the Duomo
seen from the Belvedere.

119
00:14:45,648 --> 00:14:50,274
- Do you know Florence?
- All that detail just from memory, sir?

120
00:14:50,402 --> 00:14:54,447
Memory, Agent Starling,
is what I have instead of a view.

121
00:14:54,573 --> 00:15:00,446
Well, perhaps you'd care to lend us
your view on this questionnaire, sir.

122
00:15:00,579 --> 00:15:03,283
Oh, no, no, no, no.

123
00:15:03,414 --> 00:15:08,290
You were doing fine. You had been
courteous and receptive to courtesy.

124
00:15:08,419 --> 00:15:12,879
You had established trust, with
the embarrassing truth about Miggs.

125
00:15:13,006 --> 00:15:17,751
And now this ham-handed segue
into your questionnaire.

126
00:15:19,012 --> 00:15:22,546
- It won't do.
- I'm only asking you to look at this.

127
00:15:22,681 --> 00:15:24,721
Either you will or you won't.

128
00:15:24,850 --> 00:15:28,634
Yeah. Jack Crawford
must be very busy indeed

129
00:15:28,771 --> 00:15:31,558
if he's recruiting help
from the student body.

130
00:15:31,690 --> 00:15:34,477
Busy hunting that new one: Buffalo Bill.

131
00:15:34,610 --> 00:15:36,850
What a naughty boy he is.

132
00:15:37,277 --> 00:15:40,527
Do you know why he's called Buffalo Bill?

133
00:15:40,655 --> 00:15:44,071
Please tell me.
The newspapers won't say.

134
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:47,781
It started as a bad joke
in Kansas City Homicide.

135
00:15:47,913 --> 00:15:52,005
They said
"This one likes to skin his humps."

136
00:15:53,262 --> 00:15:58,719
Why do you think he removes
their skins, Agent Starling?

137
00:15:58,851 --> 00:16:01,093
Thrill me with your acumen.

138
00:16:01,811 --> 00:16:07,316
It excites him. Most serial killers keep
some sort of trophies from their victims.

139
00:16:07,442 --> 00:16:11,521
- I didn't.
- No. No, you ate yours.

140
00:16:14,281 --> 00:16:16,320
You send that through now.

141
00:16:43,433 --> 00:16:48,426
Oh, Agent Starling, you think you can
dissect me with this blunt little tool?

142
00:16:48,562 --> 00:16:51,516
No. I thought that your knowledge...

143
00:16:51,648 --> 00:16:53,890
You're so ambitious, aren't you?

144
00:16:54,276 --> 00:16:57,894
Do you know what you look like, with
your good bag and your cheap shoes?

145
00:16:58,029 --> 00:17:00,105
You look like a rube.

146
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:04,319
A well-scrubbed, hustling rube,
with a little taste.

147
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,449
Good nutrition's given you length of bone,

148
00:17:07,579 --> 00:17:12,822
but you're not more than one generation
from poor white trash, are you?

149
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:17,953
And that accent you've tried so
desperately to shed: Pure West Virginia.

150
00:17:18,089 --> 00:17:22,252
What is your father, dear? Is he
a coal miner? Does he stink of the lamp?

151
00:17:22,385 --> 00:17:25,136
How quickly the boys found you.

152
00:17:25,263 --> 00:17:28,880
All those tedious, sticky fumblings
in the back seats of cars,

153
00:17:29,015 --> 00:17:32,527
while you could only dream of
getting out, getting anywhere,

154
00:17:32,656 --> 00:17:36,818
getting all the way to the FBI.

155
00:17:39,703 --> 00:17:42,539
You see a lot, Doctor.

156
00:17:42,665 --> 00:17:48,750
But are you strong enough to point
that high-powered perception at yourself?

157
00:17:48,879 --> 00:17:54,547
What about it? Why don't you look at
yourself and write down what you see?

158
00:17:54,675 --> 00:17:57,130
Or maybe you're afraid to.

159
00:18:06,061 --> 00:18:09,061
A census taker once tried to test me.

160
00:18:09,188 --> 00:18:12,473
I ate his liver with some fava beans

161
00:18:12,608 --> 00:18:15,063
and a nice Chianti.

162
00:18:23,702 --> 00:18:26,868
You fly back to school now, little Starling.

163
00:18:26,996 --> 00:18:28,574
Fly, fly, fly.

164
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:47,800
I bit my wrist so I can die.

165
00:18:49,142 --> 00:18:51,181
Look at the blood!

166
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:55,224
- Got ya!
- Miggs, you stupid fuck!

167
00:18:58,065 --> 00:19:01,065
- I'm gonna kill him!
- Agent Starling! Come back!

168
00:19:01,193 --> 00:19:05,107
Agent Starling! Agent Starling!
I would not have had that happen to you.

169
00:19:05,238 --> 00:19:08,275
- Discourtesy is unspeakably ugly.
- Then do this test.

170
00:19:08,408 --> 00:19:11,540
No, but I'll give you a chance
for what you love most.

171
00:19:11,673 --> 00:19:14,508
- And what is that?
- Advancement. Listen carefully.

172
00:19:14,634 --> 00:19:17,255
Look deep within yourself,
Clarice Starling.

173
00:19:17,386 --> 00:19:21,254
Go seek out Miss Mofet,
an old patient of mine. M-O-F-E-T.

174
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:26,597
I don't think Miggs could manage again
so soon, even though he is crazy. Go!

175
00:20:08,515 --> 00:20:10,554
Hey, Bill.

176
00:20:14,396 --> 00:20:16,851
- Daddy!
- Hey, Clarice.

177
00:20:20,443 --> 00:20:25,650
- Did you get any bad guys today, Daddy?
- No, angel. They all got away today.

178
00:20:46,008 --> 00:20:48,250
FBI. Hands up. Don't move.

179
00:20:48,386 --> 00:20:52,347
Turn around.
Hands behind your back. Thumbs up.

180
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:58,234
You're dead, Starling.

181
00:20:58,365 --> 00:21:02,493
Johnson, good entry, good command.
Starling, where's your danger area?

182
00:21:02,619 --> 00:21:04,030
- The corner.
- Did you check?

183
00:21:04,162 --> 00:21:05,870
- No.
- That's why you're dead.

184
00:21:06,164 --> 00:21:08,240
3109.

185
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:11,624
3109. Breaking doors or windows

186
00:21:11,752 --> 00:21:14,586
to enter or exit.

187
00:21:14,712 --> 00:21:16,088
Rule 404.

188
00:21:34,981 --> 00:21:39,144
- Clarice, phone. It's the guru.
- Crawford? Thanks, Ardelia.

189
00:21:39,485 --> 00:21:42,106
- Starling?
- Sir?

190
00:21:42,237 --> 00:21:44,645
Miggs is dead.

191
00:21:44,782 --> 00:21:46,525
Dead?

192
00:21:46,658 --> 00:21:48,116
How?

193
00:21:48,242 --> 00:21:51,777
They heard Lecter whispering to him
all afternoon and Miggs crying.

194
00:21:51,913 --> 00:21:56,075
They found him at bed check.
He'd swallowed his own tongue.

195
00:21:57,542 --> 00:22:00,876
- Starling?
- Yeah. I'm still here, sir.

196
00:22:01,004 --> 00:22:04,170
I just... I don't know how to feel about this.

197
00:22:04,757 --> 00:22:09,300
You don't have to feel any way about it.
Lecter did it to amuse himself.

198
00:22:09,428 --> 00:22:15,181
Look, I know it got ugly today, but
you mentioned a name at the end: Mofet.

199
00:22:15,309 --> 00:22:17,763
Any follow-up on her?

200
00:22:17,894 --> 00:22:21,178
Lecter altered or destroyed
most of his patients' histories,

201
00:22:21,313 --> 00:22:24,812
so there's no record
of anyone named Mofet, but

202
00:22:24,941 --> 00:22:29,188
I thought the "yourself" reference
was too hokey for Lecter,

203
00:22:29,321 --> 00:22:33,377
so I figured he's from Baltimore
and I looked in the phone book

204
00:22:33,503 --> 00:22:39,505
and there's a "Your Self" storage facility
right outside of downtown Baltimore, sir.

205
00:22:41,927 --> 00:22:47,633
Unit 31 was leased for ten years,
pre-paid in full.

206
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:52,761
The contract is in the name
of a Miss Hester Mofet.

207
00:22:53,981 --> 00:22:56,518
So nobody's been in here since 1980?

208
00:22:56,649 --> 00:22:58,938
Not to my knowledge.

209
00:22:59,068 --> 00:23:02,852
Privacy is a great concern
to my customers.

210
00:23:03,614 --> 00:23:08,360
Yes. I won't disturb anything, I promise.
I'll be outta here before you know it.

211
00:23:08,494 --> 00:23:10,783
- May I help you?
- Yes, actually.

212
00:23:17,168 --> 00:23:21,248
- It's stuck.
- We could return tomorrow with my son.

213
00:23:21,381 --> 00:23:24,167
What about him?

214
00:23:24,299 --> 00:23:29,091
I would ask my driver to help you,
but he detests physical labour.

215
00:23:30,096 --> 00:23:34,010
Right. Well, you just stay here.
I'll be back in one minute.

216
00:24:07,089 --> 00:24:10,385
It's stuck. Hand me that flashlight, sir.

217
00:24:23,990 --> 00:24:28,153
If this door should fall down
or anything else,

218
00:24:29,786 --> 00:24:32,703
this is the number for
our Baltimore field office.

219
00:24:32,830 --> 00:24:36,744
Now they know that you're with me.
Call them if anything should happen.

220
00:24:36,875 --> 00:24:39,331
Yes, Miss Starling.

221
00:27:09,651 --> 00:27:13,316
Clarice. They're waiting for you.
Watch your step.

222
00:27:14,989 --> 00:27:19,068
Hester Mofet. It's an anagram,
isn't it, Doctor?

223
00:27:19,201 --> 00:27:22,321
Hester Mofet. "The rest of me."

224
00:27:22,704 --> 00:27:26,867
"Miss the rest of me."
Meaning that you rented that garage?

225
00:28:02,585 --> 00:28:06,084
- Thank you.
- Your bleeding has stopped.

226
00:28:08,549 --> 00:28:10,589
How did you...?

227
00:28:11,761 --> 00:28:14,464
It's nothing. It was just a scratch.

228
00:28:16,514 --> 00:28:18,803
Dr Lecter, whose head is in that bottle?

229
00:28:18,933 --> 00:28:22,183
Why don't you ask me about Buffalo Bill?

230
00:28:22,312 --> 00:28:26,440
- Do you know something about him?
- I might if I saw the case file.

231
00:28:26,566 --> 00:28:30,149
- You could get that for me.
- Why don't we talk about Miss Mofet?

232
00:28:30,278 --> 00:28:32,566
