895
01:34:34,945 --> 01:34:37,103
Precious!

896
01:34:37,239 --> 01:34:39,481
Are you up there, you little shit?

897
01:34:40,533 --> 01:34:43,238
Come and get it, pretty girl.

898
01:34:49,874 --> 01:34:53,540
Precious, please come. Come on.

899
01:35:15,148 --> 01:35:16,691
Would you fuck me?

900
01:35:17,109 --> 01:35:19,350
Come on. Take that bone.

901
01:35:23,948 --> 01:35:25,228
I'd fuck me.

902
01:35:26,075 --> 01:35:28,364
Come on.

903
01:35:31,330 --> 01:35:33,370
I'd fuck me hard.

904
01:35:33,499 --> 01:35:35,538
I'd fuck me so hard.

905
01:35:40,213 --> 01:35:41,374
No.

906
01:36:27,351 --> 01:36:31,762
AIR NATIONAL GUARD HQ
CHICAGO, IL

907
01:36:42,573 --> 01:36:46,404
Is that a good job, FBI agent?
You get to travel around and stuff?

908
01:36:46,534 --> 01:36:48,656
I mean, better places than this?

909
01:36:50,454 --> 01:36:52,742
Sometimes you do.

910
01:36:52,873 --> 01:36:57,285
Freddie was so happy for me
when I got this job at the bank.

911
01:36:57,419 --> 01:37:01,464
Toaster giveaways and Barry Manilow
on the speakers all day.

912
01:37:01,590 --> 01:37:04,376
She thought it was such hot shit.

913
01:37:04,508 --> 01:37:06,964
What did she know? Big dummy.

914
01:37:07,094 --> 01:37:13,049
Stacy, did Fredrica ever mention a man
named Jamie Gumb or a Jame Gumb?

915
01:37:13,851 --> 01:37:16,140
- How about John Grant?
- No.

916
01:37:16,270 --> 01:37:19,105
Would she have had a friend
you didn't know about?

917
01:37:19,231 --> 01:37:21,472
If she had a guy,
I'd have known, believe me.

918
01:37:21,607 --> 01:37:25,522
- Sewing was her life.
- Did you two ever work together?

919
01:37:25,653 --> 01:37:30,824
Sure. Me and Pam Malavesi used to help
her do alterations for old Mrs Lippman.

920
01:37:30,961 --> 01:37:34,579
Can you give me Mrs Lippman's address?
I need to talk to her.

921
01:37:35,090 --> 01:37:38,790
CALUMET CITY, IL

922
01:38:02,781 --> 01:38:05,699
So powerful. So beautiful.

923
01:38:11,247 --> 01:38:13,286
Precious?

924
01:38:18,504 --> 01:38:21,788
- Precious?
- She's down here, you sack of shit!

925
01:38:30,639 --> 01:38:35,100
- Put her in that bucket.
- Get me a telephone and lower it down.

926
01:38:38,355 --> 01:38:40,680
Poodlie-poo. Precious.

927
01:38:40,816 --> 01:38:45,393
- Darling heart, are you all right?
- She's in a lot of pain. She needs a vet.

928
01:38:49,657 --> 01:38:52,693
She broke her leg
on the way down. I know it.

929
01:38:52,826 --> 01:38:56,694
- Don't you hurt my dog!
- Don't you make me hurt your dog!

930
01:38:56,830 --> 01:38:59,037
You don't know what pain is!

931
01:39:12,523 --> 01:39:16,852
- Oh, fuck!
- You better be gettin' me that telephone!

932
01:39:17,194 --> 01:39:19,648
I'm gonna do it, mister!

933
01:39:23,866 --> 01:39:25,859
All right, mister! I'm doin' it!

934
01:39:49,182 --> 01:39:51,221
OK, I'm coming.

935
01:39:53,060 --> 01:39:55,099
We're goin' in.

936
01:39:59,232 --> 01:40:04,025
Good afternoon. Sorry to bother you.
I'm looking for Mrs Lippman's family.

937
01:40:04,696 --> 01:40:07,269
FBI! Everybody down!

938
01:40:07,407 --> 01:40:09,978
No, Lippmans don't live here any more.

939
01:40:10,116 --> 01:40:12,358
Excuse me.
I really need to speak with you.

940
01:40:13,578 --> 01:40:15,321
Clear!

941
01:40:16,164 --> 01:40:18,202
What's the problem, officer?

942
01:40:18,331 --> 01:40:21,083
I'm investigating the death
of Fredrica Bimmel.

943
01:40:24,671 --> 01:40:27,126
There's no one here, Jack.

944
01:40:28,716 --> 01:40:29,914
Clarice.

945
01:40:30,050 --> 01:40:32,802
- Your name is?
- Jack Gordon.

946
01:40:32,928 --> 01:40:38,088
Mr Gordon. Good. Well, Fredrica used to
work for Mrs Lippman. Did you know her?

947
01:40:39,100 --> 01:40:41,176
No. Uh-uh.

948
01:40:41,310 --> 01:40:42,969
Oh, wait.

949
01:40:43,103 --> 01:40:45,261
Was she a great, big, fat person?

950
01:40:46,189 --> 01:40:49,605
- She was a big girl, sir.
- Yeah, I may have...

951
01:40:49,735 --> 01:40:52,237
No, I read about her in the newspaper.

952
01:40:54,209 --> 01:40:56,747
Mrs Lippman had a son.
Maybe he could help you.

953
01:40:56,879 --> 01:40:59,831
I got his card here someplace.
Come in while I look for it.

954
01:40:59,964 --> 01:41:02,419
- May I?
- Yeah, sure.

955
01:41:21,316 --> 01:41:24,816
Are you close to catchin'
somebody, you think?

956
01:41:24,945 --> 01:41:26,984
Yes. We may be.

957
01:41:29,366 --> 01:41:34,442
Did you take over this place
after Mrs Lippman died, is that right?

958
01:41:36,455 --> 01:41:40,784
Yeah, I bought this house two years ago.

959
01:41:42,002 --> 01:41:45,454
Did she leave any records?
Any business records?

960
01:41:45,589 --> 01:41:48,875
Tax forms? List of employees?

961
01:41:49,884 --> 01:41:52,340
No, nothin' like that at all.

962
01:41:54,305 --> 01:41:57,223
Say, has the FBI learned something?

963
01:41:57,350 --> 01:42:01,182
The police around here
don't seem to have the first clue.

964
01:42:10,278 --> 01:42:16,233
I mean, have you got, like, a description,
fingerprints, anything like that?

965
01:42:16,368 --> 01:42:18,407
No.

966
01:42:19,996 --> 01:42:22,035
No, we don't.

967
01:42:32,727 --> 01:42:35,016
Here's that number.

968
01:42:35,772 --> 01:42:39,472
Very good, Mr Gordon.
May I use your phone, please?

969
01:42:47,616 --> 01:42:49,654
Sure, you can use my phone.

970
01:42:51,035 --> 01:42:54,155
Freeze! Put your hands over your head.

971
01:42:54,788 --> 01:42:57,907
And turn around. Spread your legs.

972
01:42:58,416 --> 01:43:01,583
Spread your legs.
Put your hands in the back. Thumbs up.

973
01:43:01,711 --> 01:43:03,751
Freeze!

974
01:44:37,852 --> 01:44:40,472
Hello? Are you there?

975
01:44:41,562 --> 01:44:44,018
I'm down here!

976
01:45:03,832 --> 01:45:06,502
- Catherine Martin?
- Yes!

977
01:45:08,754 --> 01:45:11,589
FBI. You're safe.

978
01:45:11,715 --> 01:45:14,170
Safe, shit! Get me outta here!

979
01:45:29,898 --> 01:45:33,231
- You're all right. Where is he?
- How the fuck should I know?

980
01:45:33,360 --> 01:45:37,488
- Just get me outta here!
- You gotta be quiet. Shut that dog up.

981
01:45:38,406 --> 01:45:40,482
Just get me outta here!

982
01:45:41,534 --> 01:45:43,573
Oh, my God.

983
01:45:45,245 --> 01:45:49,408
Catherine, I'm gonna get you outta there,
but right now you listen to me.

984
01:45:49,540 --> 01:45:51,794
I've gotta leave this room. Be right back.

985
01:45:51,930 --> 01:45:55,760
No! Don't you leave me here,
you fuckin' bitch!

986
01:45:55,891 --> 01:45:59,758
Don't you leave me here!
This guy's fuckin' crazy!

987
01:46:02,813 --> 01:46:04,687
Please!

988
01:46:04,815 --> 01:46:07,602
I gotta get outta here!

989
01:46:10,196 --> 01:46:14,941
Catherine, the other officers'll
be here any minute now.

990
01:46:15,075 --> 01:46:19,025
Wait! Don't go! Please!

991
01:46:19,163 --> 01:46:20,407
Quiet!

992
01:50:21,279 --> 01:50:24,363
- You OK?
- Gunpowder. It's nothing. I'm OK.

993
01:50:24,490 --> 01:50:26,779
How did you track Buffalo Bill here?

994
01:50:33,164 --> 01:50:35,204
Clarice M Starling.

995
01:50:38,044 --> 01:50:40,084
Congratulations.

996
01:51:13,631 --> 01:51:15,836
Special Agent Starling.

997
01:51:15,966 --> 01:51:18,587
- Special Agent Mapp.
- Phone call.

998
01:51:18,718 --> 01:51:20,758
- Excuse me.
- Starling.

999
01:51:23,722 --> 01:51:26,178
Pilch, could you take our picture?

1000
01:51:26,308 --> 01:51:28,348
Yeah. Sure.

1001
01:51:29,269 --> 01:51:32,305
Look, I just wanted
to say congratulations.

1002
01:51:32,438 --> 01:51:36,139
I'm not much good at this kinda thing,
so I'm gonna duck outta here.

1003
01:51:36,275 --> 01:51:38,315
OK. Sure.

1004
01:51:39,278 --> 01:51:41,733
Thank you, Mr Crawford.

1005
01:51:49,036 --> 01:51:52,239
Your father would have been proud today.

1006
01:51:54,416 --> 01:51:56,871
Don't forget your phone call.

1007
01:52:00,922 --> 01:52:04,006
- Starling.
- Well, Clarice?

1008
01:52:04,592 --> 01:52:07,047
Have the lambs stopped screaming?

1009
01:52:07,470 --> 01:52:09,842
- Dr Lecter.
- Don't bother with the trace.

1010
01:52:09,972 --> 01:52:11,846
I won't be on long enough.

1011
01:52:15,435 --> 01:52:19,646
- Where are you, Dr Lecter?
- I have no plans to call on you, Clarice.

1012
01:52:19,773 --> 01:52:22,725
The world's more interesting
with you in it.

1013
01:52:22,858 --> 01:52:25,894
So you take care now
to extend me the same courtesy.

1014
01:52:26,028 --> 01:52:28,483
You know I can't make that promise.

1015
01:52:28,947 --> 01:52:31,330
I do wish we could chat longer but...

1016
01:52:32,754 --> 01:52:35,624
I'm having an old friend for dinner.

1017
01:52:36,841 --> 01:52:39,379
- Bye.
- Dr Lecter?

1018
01:52:42,388 --> 01:52:44,428
Dr Lecter?

1019
01:52:52,314 --> 01:52:55,268
Excuse me. You got
the security system all set up?

1020
01:52:55,400 --> 01:52:59,611
- We have the big-shot security.
- Thank you. I appreciate that.